Pan values seem to be ignored when playing back Sound instances on Mac OSX. Use the following code to reproduce:

```
import com.badlogic.gdx.Audio;
import com.badlogic.gdx.Files;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglFiles;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglNativesLoader;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.audio.OpenALAudio;

public class GDXSoundPanDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        LwjglNativesLoader.load();
        Files files = new LwjglFiles();
        Audio audio = new OpenALAudio();
        audio.newSound(files.absolute("/Users/krueger/sounds/loops/flowing_river.wav")).play(1, 1, 1);
    }
}
```

This should pan to the right but whatever value I use for pan, the sound is played in the center. Tested with libgdx 1.5.5 on OSX 10.10.2.

Hi,

I am not able to get a Music instance to loop on OSX. Use the following sample code to reproduce:

import com.badlogic.gdx.Audio;
import com.badlogic.gdx.Files;
import com.badlogic.gdx.audio.Music;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglFiles;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglNativesLoader;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.audio.OpenALAudio;

public class GDXMusicLoopDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        LwjglNativesLoader.load();
        Files files = new LwjglFiles();
        Audio audio = new OpenALAudio();
        final Music music = audio.newMusic(files.absolute("/Users/krueger/sounds/loops/flowing_river.wav"));
        music.setLooping(true);
        music.play();
    }
}

The sound is only played back once. Expected behaviour would be for it to loop. Tried with libgdx version 1.5.5 on OSX 10.10.2. 
Note that looping works fine on OSX when using Sound instead of Music.

